13:00.513 --> 13:02.281
Not exactly,
perhaps.

13:02.281 --> 13:04.517
Yours was a bullet
in the hip.

13:04.517 --> 13:10.122
For me, it was a Lufthansa
steward named Gunter.

13:11.791 --> 13:12.625
What did I tell you?

13:12.625 --> 13:13.626
I knew they'd hit it off.

13:14.126 --> 13:17.062
Yes, I had a
feeling myself.

13:17.062 --> 13:20.866
And you didn't say
a word, you scamp.

13:20.866 --> 13:23.269
Uh, Frasier,
why don't you come

13:23.269 --> 13:26.272
help me get some snacks
for everybody?

13:26.272 --> 13:27.740
All right.

13:27.740 --> 13:30.543
If you'll excuse us.

13:30.543 --> 13:31.811
You didn't tell me
this was a setup.

13:31.811 --> 13:33.312
Well, how blind
can you be, Dad?

13:33.312 --> 13:34.814
He didn't seem gay
to you?

13:34.814 --> 13:36.315
He's English;
they all seem gay.

13:36.315 --> 13:37.316
Oh, Lord.

13:37.316 --> 13:39.318
Well, we're just going to
have to tell them the truth.

13:39.318 --> 13:41.320
Oh, what, you found
her mother so unattractive

13:41.320 --> 13:42.321
you pretended to be gay?

13:42.822 --> 13:44.323
Dad, Emily is
the most fabulous woman

13:44.323 --> 13:45.324
I have met in ages,

13:45.324 --> 13:46.325
and if you screw
this up for me,

13:46.826 --> 13:47.326
I will never forgive you,

13:47.827 --> 13:48.694
so just be nice,
all right?

13:48.694 --> 13:50.329
Well, what if he asks me
for a date?

13:50.329 --> 13:52.031
I have news for you:
You're on a date.

13:53.999 --> 13:55.467
Daphne.
We've just been chatting

13:55.968 --> 13:58.470
with your delightful
physical therapist, Marty.

13:58.470 --> 14:00.706
Oh, he's a charmer,
this one.

14:00.706 --> 14:02.341
Now aren't you
glad you went

14:02.341 --> 14:03.108
to the opera?

14:03.108 --> 14:05.077
I keep telling him
he should get out more,

14:05.077 --> 14:05.911
meet people.

14:05.911 --> 14:07.780
Most nights
he just sits here alone

14:07.780 --> 14:08.714
watching the telly.

14:08.714 --> 14:10.649
He's the exact same way.

14:10.649 --> 14:12.151
He'll watch anything.
Yeah.

14:12.151 --> 14:13.986
With him, it's
mostly sports.

14:13.986 --> 14:15.754
Just give him a bunch
of sweaty men

14:15.754 --> 14:17.156
chasing each other
around a field...

14:17.156 --> 14:18.924
Daphne.

14:18.924 --> 14:20.826
Excuse me.

14:20.826 --> 14:23.329
Where are we, uh, keeping
the Camembert these days?

14:23.329 --> 14:24.330
Same place
we always do.

14:24.330 --> 14:25.664
(under breath):
Get in the kitchen.

14:25.664 --> 14:27.666
You were smart
to hire a woman

14:27.666 --> 14:28.667
for physical therapy.

14:28.667 --> 14:31.036
Much safer than a man.

14:31.036 --> 14:32.404
Edward sprained
his leg last year...

14:32.404 --> 14:33.272
All right, Emily.

14:33.272 --> 14:35.174
I never trusted
that man.

14:35.174 --> 14:36.175
All right, Emily.

14:36.175 --> 14:37.676
And why you loaned
him your boat...

14:37.676 --> 14:40.045
(under breath):
All right, Emily!

14:41.814 --> 14:44.183
(Daphne laughing)

14:48.487 --> 14:49.989
Here we are.

14:49.989 --> 14:50.890
Thank you,
Frasier.

14:50.890 --> 14:52.691
I would love to see

14:52.691 --> 14:55.694
the rest of the apartment,
if it's no trouble.

14:56.262 --> 14:58.063
Why, that's no
trouble at all.

14:58.063 --> 14:59.798
Uh, Frasier, can-can I just...
Now, Dad,

14:59.798 --> 15:00.799
don't worry.

15:00.799 --> 15:02.801
I will close the door
to your room.

15:02.801 --> 15:04.803
You should see him whenever
he gets ready for the opera.

15:04.803 --> 15:07.172
Clothes everywhere.

15:08.874 --> 15:10.209
Well, I'm off to bed.

15:10.209 --> 15:11.644
Oh, no, no, no.
Uh, Daph!

15:11.644 --> 15:13.145
Uh, Daphne,
why don't you join us?

15:13.145 --> 15:14.480
Oh, no, no, no.

15:14.480 --> 15:16.815
Three's a crowd.

15:21.287 --> 15:22.588
So...

15:22.588 --> 15:23.889
(both laughing)

15:23.889 --> 15:26.191
So...

15:26.191 --> 15:29.361
Our loved ones seemed determined
to thrust us together.

15:29.361 --> 15:31.764
Well, don't let
them pressure you.

15:33.065 --> 15:34.833
Oh.

15:36.302 --> 15:38.537
Congratulations, Marty,
on having raised

15:38.537 --> 15:40.306
such a splendid son.

15:40.306 --> 15:43.309
Oh.
I envy you your bond.

15:45.244 --> 15:46.211
Uh, you have kids?

15:46.211 --> 15:47.713
Just one.

15:47.713 --> 15:51.050
George. He's 35...

15:51.050 --> 15:54.320
and he has consecrated
his life to bowling.

15:54.320 --> 15:55.688
Oh.

15:55.688 --> 15:57.589
I join him
when I can, but...

15:57.589 --> 15:58.590
You're not
wild about it.

15:58.590 --> 15:59.992
No. I mean...

15:59.992 --> 16:02.361
the shoes.

16:02.361 --> 16:03.829
(Martin laughs)

16:03.829 --> 16:05.631
Strange, isn't it,

16:05.631 --> 16:07.366
the-the things we'll do
to be close to our children?

16:07.366 --> 16:08.767
Oh, yeah.

16:08.767 --> 16:10.269
I've let Frasier drag me

16:10.269 --> 16:12.271
to all kinds of places
I didn't want to go to

16:12.271 --> 16:14.106
just so that I could
spend some time with him.

16:14.106 --> 16:15.441
You know, sometimes,

16:15.441 --> 16:17.943
it's hard to humor
your kids, but...

16:17.943 --> 16:19.945
It's what we do.

16:19.945 --> 16:20.946
We're fathers.

16:20.946 --> 16:22.448
Exactly.

16:22.448 --> 16:24.283
Marty...

16:24.283 --> 16:26.752
would you be free
for dinner sometime?

16:27.686 --> 16:30.522
Oh, gee, I, uh...

16:30.522 --> 16:31.824
It's all right.
Never mind.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.826
No, no, no, no, I-I-I
mean, I'd love to.

16:33.826 --> 16:34.827
It's just that, uh...

16:34.827 --> 16:36.328
No need to explain.

16:36.328 --> 16:37.763
No, no, really, Ed,

16:37.763 --> 16:39.198
it's not you--
you're a great guy.

16:39.198 --> 16:44.603
It's just that I'm...
dating someone.

16:45.971 --> 16:48.707
Marty, you don't have
to spare my feelings.

16:48.707 --> 16:50.275
No, no, really, it's true.

16:50.275 --> 16:52.044
Hello.
Darling!

17:00.252 --> 17:01.253
Sorry.

17:01.754 --> 17:02.654
Am I interrupting
something?

17:02.654 --> 17:04.056
Oh, not a thing, honey.

17:04.056 --> 17:06.392
Just take off your coat
and stay a while.

17:09.127 --> 17:09.962
Okay, um...

17:09.962 --> 17:11.797
I, uh, I felt bad

17:11.797 --> 17:13.298
about that
squabble earlier,

17:13.799 --> 17:15.300
so I thought
I'd drop off

17:15.800 --> 17:16.667
this little
peace offering.

17:16.667 --> 17:17.502
(laughs)

17:17.502 --> 17:20.806
As if I could stay mad
at you.

17:22.441 --> 17:24.843
Uh, Edward, uh, this is
my boyfriend, Niles.

17:24.843 --> 17:28.347
Uh... Niles, uh,
this is Edward.

17:28.847 --> 17:29.848
We met at the opera
tonight.

17:29.848 --> 17:31.316
Delighted.
Hello.

17:31.316 --> 17:32.251
You needn't look
so startled.

17:32.251 --> 17:35.054
I assure you,
there's nothing funny going on.

17:35.054 --> 17:37.890
Oh, good.

17:39.658 --> 17:42.928
Well, uh, why don't
we go put this on ice?

17:46.932 --> 17:49.401
Of course, the finest
Gilda ever sung

17:49.401 --> 17:52.404
was by the great
Mathilde DeCagny.

17:52.404 --> 17:53.906
I actually have
the recording.

17:53.906 --> 17:56.408
I'd love to hear it.

17:56.408 --> 17:57.743
Where's Dad?

17:57.743 --> 18:00.079
He's in the kitchen
with his boyfriend.

18:02.014 --> 18:03.949
FRASIER:
Oh.

18:09.855 --> 18:12.791
Niles, what
brings you here?

18:12.791 --> 18:14.760
Well, it's my place, too.

18:15.227 --> 18:16.762
I can have company
if I want.

18:17.262 --> 18:18.730
Emily, this is Niles.

18:18.730 --> 18:20.666
Hello.
Hi.

18:20.666 --> 18:21.467
Um...

18:21.467 --> 18:22.801
I didn't realize

18:22.801 --> 18:24.303
your father
was seeing someone.

18:24.303 --> 18:25.804
Well, actually, I-I
didn't think he was.

18:25.804 --> 18:29.308
Um... since when
are you two an item?

18:29.308 --> 18:30.576
MARTIN:
Oh.

18:30.576 --> 18:31.844
Few weeks now.

18:31.844 --> 18:33.846
We-we didn't say anything
about it yet,

18:33.846 --> 18:37.816
because... well...

18:37.816 --> 18:40.819
So many reasons.

18:40.819 --> 18:41.854
You know,

18:41.854 --> 18:43.288
it's getting late, Emily.

18:43.288 --> 18:44.289
EMILY:
Oh, yes.

18:44.289 --> 18:45.290
We should be going.

18:45.791 --> 18:46.291
No, no, please, please,

18:46.792 --> 18:47.292
stay for just
five more minutes.

18:47.793 --> 18:49.795
I-I have a very special
old port

18:49.795 --> 18:51.797
that I'd love
for you to sample.

18:51.797 --> 18:53.298
(whispering):
Niles.

18:57.236 --> 18:58.237
How could
you do this to me?

18:58.237 --> 18:59.738
This was not my idea.

18:59.738 --> 19:02.741
Niles... Emily just kissed me
in the bedroom,

19:03.242 --> 19:04.243
and now she's leaving.

19:04.243 --> 19:06.245
I have never been
so embarrassed in my life.

19:06.245 --> 19:07.212
You're embarrassed?

19:07.212 --> 19:11.683
They think the best I can do
is an old man with a cane.

19:14.052 --> 19:15.888
You have got
to fix this.

19:15.888 --> 19:17.189
Oh, and how am I
supposed to do that?

19:17.189 --> 19:19.925
Well, isn't it obvious?
You've got to dump Dad.

19:20.893 --> 19:22.394
Ah, here we are.

19:22.394 --> 19:24.163
You really must

19:24.163 --> 19:25.430
try this.

19:25.430 --> 19:26.431
Thank you.

19:26.431 --> 19:27.933
Mm-hmm.

19:27.933 --> 19:29.368
So, Niles,
you actually,

19:29.368 --> 19:32.104
uh, missed a-a splendid evening
at the opera.

19:32.104 --> 19:32.905
Well, maybe I
can catch it

19:32.905 --> 19:34.406
this weekend
with Mel.

19:34.406 --> 19:35.407
Oh, and who's Mel?

19:35.407 --> 19:36.909
Damn you and your
jealous questions!

19:36.909 --> 19:38.744
You don't own me!

19:43.882 --> 19:45.217
MARTIN:
Niles!

19:45.217 --> 19:46.985
I was only asking.
You're always asking,

19:46.985 --> 19:48.453
badgering, spying on me.

19:48.453 --> 19:50.255
Well, I won't
be suffocated anymore.

19:50.255 --> 19:52.057
I'm tired of being
your trophy boy.

19:52.057 --> 19:53.859
It's over,
you hear me? Over!

19:54.693 --> 19:57.529
And I'm keeping the jewelry.

20:04.403 --> 20:06.705
Oh, Dad.

20:06.705 --> 20:09.107
I'm so sorry.

20:11.743 --> 20:15.581
Is there anything we can do?

20:15.581 --> 20:17.049
No, I'll be all right. I...

20:17.549 --> 20:20.052
I guess I always knew
it wouldn't last.

20:20.052 --> 20:21.453
Marty...

20:21.453 --> 20:23.755
the young ones never stay.

20:25.123 --> 20:27.526
I know what will cheer you up.

20:27.526 --> 20:28.894
That Rigoletto recording.

20:28.894 --> 20:30.395
Oh, yes, splendid.

20:30.395 --> 20:31.396
You know, Emily,
I'd love to hear it,

20:31.396 --> 20:32.898
but that shipment
is arriving

20:32.898 --> 20:33.899
bright and early.

20:33.899 --> 20:35.901
Oh, right.

20:35.901 --> 20:37.903
Uh, Frasier,

20:37.903 --> 20:40.372
I wish I could stay,

20:40.372 --> 20:42.207
but I'm Edward's ride.

20:42.207 --> 20:44.009
FRASIER:
Yes, what a shame.

20:44.009 --> 20:45.510
Well, I-I guess this
is good night, then.

20:45.978 --> 20:46.979
MARTIN:
No, no, wait a minute.

20:46.979 --> 20:48.914
Emily, uh...

20:48.914 --> 20:50.415
why don't you just
stay here with Frasier

20:50.415 --> 20:53.252
and enjoy the music.

20:53.252 --> 20:55.954
I'll give Edward a ride home.

20:55.954 --> 20:57.623
You would do
that, Dad?

20:58.323 --> 21:00.826
Happy Valentine's Day, son.

21:01.793 --> 21:03.595
Thanks, Dad.
All right,

21:03.595 --> 21:04.930
good night.
Good night.

21:04.930 --> 21:06.331
BOTH:
Good night.

21:07.799 --> 21:09.801
(music playing)

21:09.801 --> 21:13.305
It was so sweet
of your father to do that.

21:13.305 --> 21:17.309
He really loves you,
doesn't he?

21:17.309 --> 21:18.810
(chuckles)

21:18.810 --> 21:21.313
You have no idea.

21:26.585 --> 21:28.587
♪ Hey, baby, I hear the blues
a'callin' ♪

21:29.087 --> 21:31.189
♪ Tossed salads
and scrambled eggs ♪

21:31.189 --> 21:33.191
♪ Quite stylish ♪

21:33.191 --> 21:35.627
♪ And maybe
I seem a bit confused ♪

21:35.627 --> 21:38.697
♪ Well, maybe,
but I got you pegged ♪

21:38.697 --> 21:40.532
(laughing)

21:40.532 --> 21:42.367
♪ But I don't know what to do ♪

21:42.367 --> 21:46.371
♪ With those tossed salads
and scrambled eggs ♪

21:46.371 --> 21:48.874
♪ They're callin' again. ♪

21:48.874 --> 21:52.778
Thank you!

